public class EditContractorDialog
extends javax.swing.JDialog

Dialog that displays and allows to edit the properties of a contractor. Currently, only the editing of the owner field is supported; however, this could be easily extended.

Version:
1.0
Author:

Method Detail

bookContractor

public final BookResult bookContractor(long recNo,
                                       Contractor contractor,
                                       BusinessServices businessServices)
Configures the dialog as a book contractor dialog and displays it. Returns when the dialog has been made invisible after confirmation or cancellation.

Parameters:
recNo - the number of the contractor record to book
contractor - the contractor object corresponding to the given recNo
businessServices - an object implementing the BusinessServices interface for the book request to the model
Returns:
a BookResult with BookStatus and Contractor if booking was actually attempted (OK button pressed), otherwise (Cancel button pressed) null.

deactivate

public final void deactivate()
Displays a notification dialog about the server being shut down regardless of whether the edit contractor dialog itself is currently visible or not.
